      },
      "date": "2012-11-02 18:43:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nInstead of all the inline #ifdefs, it would be better to have a compat wrapper for this code, like:\n\n#ifdef HAVE_DENTRY_D_ALIAS_HLIST\n#define ll_d_hlist_node hlist_node\n#define ll_d_hlist_empty(list) hlist_empty(list)\n#define ll_d_hlist_entry(ptr, type, name) hlist_entry(ptr, type, name)\n#define ll_d_hlist_for_each(tmp, i_dentry) hlist_for_each(tmp, i_dentry)\n#define ll_d_hlist_for_each_entry(denty, p, i_dentry, alias) \\\n        hlist_for_each_entry(dentry, p, i_dentry, alias)\n#else\n#define ll_d_hlist_node list_head \n#define ll_d_hlist_empty(list) list_empty(list)\n#define ll_d_hlist_entry(ptr, type, name) list_entry(ptr, type, name)\n#define ll_d_hlist_for_each(tmp, i_dentry) list_for_each(tmp, i_dentry)\n#define ll_d_hlist_for_each_entry(denty, p, i_dentry, alias) \\\n        p = NULL; list_for_each_entry(dentry, i_dentry, alias)\n#endif\n\nThe \"p = NULL\" is an attempt to quiet the \"unused variable\" warning, not sure if it will work.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
